<sect2 id="gimp-colors-tone-mapping-menu" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>The <quote>Tone Mapping</quote> Submenu</title>

  <indexterm>
    <primary>Colors</primary>
    <secondary>Tone Mapping</secondary>
  </indexterm>

  <para>
    The <guimenuitem>Tone Mapping</guimenuitem> submenu contains operations that
    allow you to use tone mapping to adjust the colors of images. Most of the
    filters provide ways to adjust High Dynamic Range images (HDR) to
    presentation using a low dynamic range.
  </para>

  <para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="gimp-filter-fattal-2002"/></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="gimp-filter-mantiuk-2006"/></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="gimp-filter-reinhard-2005 "/></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="gimp-filter-stress"/></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="plug-in-destripe"/></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para><xref linkend="plug-in-retinex"/></para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </para>

  <sect3>
    <title>Activating the Command</title>
    <para>
      You can access this command from the main menu through
      <menuchoice>
        <guimenu>Colors</guimenu>
        <guimenuitem>Tone Mapping</guimenuitem>
      </menuchoice>.
    </para>
  </sect3>

</sect2>
